      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. The \"Sapphire\" stereotype: overly emotional, aggressive, and often portrayed as a troublemaker.\n2. The \"Magical Negro\" trope: a black character who has supernatural abilities or wisdom to help the white protagonist.\n3. The \"Strong Black Man\" stereotype: a hyper-masculine black character who is physically powerful and emotionally stoic.\n4. The \"Nerdy Black Friend\" trope: a black character who is always the comic relief or sidekick, often with little depth or agency.\n5. The \"Exotic Black Woman\" stereotype: a black woman who is portrayed as overly sexualized, submissive, or exotic.\n\nThese stereotypes are harmful and perpetuate negative and inaccurate representations of black people. Avoid using them in your screenplay. Instead, strive for authentic and diverse characters that reflect the rich complexity of real people.",
