      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. so it seems like for most groups, the tropes are pretty much centered around being either hyper-violent/dangerous or just being sexualized. do you think there are any \"positive\" stereotypes that are actually used for white characters that might be considered tropes too? like, even if they're \"good\" things, they still flatten people out right?",
